44 (2) Within 45 calendar days of receiving a guidance document provided for in
45 paragraph (1) of this subsection, the Department of Education shall include on the
46 dedicated web page provided for in subsection (d) of this Code section a written response
47 to such guidance document that includes, at a minimum:
48 (A) Each federal or state statute, regulation, or rule that is addressed either expressly
49 or by reasonable implication, interpretation, or application in such guidance document;
50 and
51 (B) A description of how such guidance document will be implemented or objected to.
52 (3) Within 15 calendar days of a guidance document provided for in paragraph (1) of this
53 subsection being rescinded, the Department of Education shall:
54 (A) Clearly indicate on the dedicated web page provided for in subsection (c) of this
55 Code section that such guidance document has been rescinded; and
56 (B) Add the rescinded guidance document along with the date such guidance document
57 was rescinded to a separate and clearly identifiable list of rescinded guidance
58 documents to be maintained on the dedicated web page provided for in subsection (c)
59 of this Code section.
60 (d) All guidance documents and rescinded guidance documents which are required to be
61 published by the Department of Education under subsection (c) of this Code section shall
62 be published on a dedicated web page on the Department of Education's public website that
63 is clearly identifiable, readily searchable using the search tool included on such public
64 website, and accessible via a link that is included on the home page of such public website.
65 (e) the State School Superintendent shall report the above to the General Assembly
66 annually.
67 (f) The State Board of Education shall be authorized to adopt rules as necessary to
68 implement the requirements of this Code section. Reserved."
