70 Said title is further amended in Article 2 of Chapter 2B, relating to promise scholarship
71 accounts, by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
72 "20-2B-22.1.
73 (a) Except as provided in subsection (b) of this Code section, notwithstanding any
74 provision of paragraph (2) or (3) of subsection (a) of Code Section 20-2B-22 or any other
75 provision of law to the contrary, each student whose parent is an active duty military
76 service member stationed in Georgia shall qualify for a promise scholarship account.
77 (b) Subject to subsection (c) of this Code section:
78 (1) No student shall qualify for the first time for a promise scholarship account
79 exclusively pursuant to this Code section during any school year for which the amount
80 of funds appropriated for the program is less than the amount of funds necessary to
81 include all students who meet the family income requirement provided for in
82 subparagraph (a)(5)(A) of Code Section 20-2B-22; and
83 (2) In the event that the amount of funds appropriated for the program exceeds the
84 amount of funds necessary to include all students who meet the family income
85 requirement provided for in subparagraph (a)(5)(A) of Code Section 20-2B-22, students
86 who qualify for a promise scholarship account exclusively pursuant to this Code section
87 shall be prioritized over students whose family income exceeds 400 percent of the federal
88 poverty level as defined annually by the federal Office of Management and Budget.
89 (c) Provided that such student resides in Georgia, each student who has qualified for a
90 promise scholarship account under this Code section shall continue to be eligible to receive
91 account funds until such student returns to a public school, graduates from high school, or
92 reaches the age of 20 years, or for special education students, reaches the age of 21 years."
93 SECTION 3.
